{{Orphan|date=December 2012}} {{Infobox manuscript <!----------Name----------> | name = Abhisamayālankārāloka | location = <!----------Image----------> | image = | width = | caption = <!----------General----------> | Also known as = Illumination of the ''Abhisamayālankāra'' | Type = Buddhist | Date = 750 | Place of origin = | Language(s) = [[Sanskrit]], [[Standard Tibetan|Tibetan]] | Scribe(s) = | Author(s) = [[Haribhadra]] | Compiled by = | Illuminated by = | Patron = | Dedicated to = <!----------Form and content----------> | Material = | Size = | Format = | Condition = | Script = | Contents = | Illumination(s) = | Additions = | Exemplar(s) = | Previously kept = | Discovered = | Other = | below = }}
'''''Abhisamayalankaraloka''''' is "a commentary, by [[Haribhadra (Seng-ge Bzang-po)|Haribhadra]],<ref name=EB>{{cite encyclopedia |editor-first=Dale H. |editor-last=Hoiberg|encyclopedia=Encyclopædia Britannica |title=Abhisamayālankārāloka |edition = 15th |year=2010|publisher=Encyclopædia Britannica Inc. |volume=I: A-ak Bayes |location=Chicago, IL |isbn=978-1-59339-837-8|pages=31}}</ref> on the Asta-sahasrika-prajnaparamita-sutra."<ref>{{cite book|title=Buddhism: A Modern Perspective|first=Charles|last=Prebish|publisher=Penn State Press|year=1975|page=259|isbn=9780271011950}}</ref> This text is one of the most studied in [[Tibetan monasteries]].<ref name=EB/> At present, there are still commentaries on this "commentary" being written and studied. Around the 10th or 11th century, it was translated into [[Old Tibetan|Tibetan]].<ref name=EB/>
The Abhisamayalankaraloka was first edited by [[Giuseppe Tucci]], in Gaekwad's Oriental Series, No. 26. Later, [[Unrai Wogihara]] edited it with the text of the Astasdhasrika-prajflfiparamita-sfitra.<ref>{{cite book|title=Indian Buddhism: A Survey with Bibliographical Notes|first=Hajime|last=Nakamura|publisher=Motilal Banarsidass|year=1980|isbn=9788120802728}}</ref>
