{{Infobox officeholder | name = Ali Ibn Abd ArRahman AlHuthaify | office = Imam of [[Al-Masjid al-Nabawi]] | native_name = علي عبد الرحمان علي أحمد الحذيفي | native_name_lang = ar | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1947}} | birth_place = , [[Makkah Region]], [[Saudi Arabia]]<ref>https://archive.org/stream/ImaamMasjidNabawiSaudiEra13451436AbdullahAhmedAlGhamidi/ImaamMasjidNabawiSaudiEra-1345-1436-AbdullahAhmedAlGhamidi#page/n466</ref> | honorific-prefix = [[Sheikh]] | term_start = 1979&nbsp;– present | post = Imam and Khateeb of [[Al-Masjid al-Nabawi]], [[Medina]] | lineage = | father = Abd ArRahman Ibn Ali Ibn Ahmad Ibn Ali Ibn Abd ArRahman AlHuthaify | school = [[Hanbali]] }} '''Ali Ibn Abd ArRahman AlHuthaify''' (Al huthaifah) is an [[imam]] and [[khatib|khateeb]] of the [[Al-Masjid al-Nabawi|Great mosque of Medina]], and a former Imam of [[Quba Mosque]]. He was a lecturer of [[fiqh|Islamic jurisprudence]] and [[tawheed]] at the [[Islamic University of Madinah]]. His style of reciting the Quran in a slow, deep tune is widely recognised.<ref>http://www.assabile.com/ali-al-hodhaifi-19/ali-al-hodhaifi.htm</ref>
==Life and career== '''Ali AlHuthaify''' grew up in a religious the family. His father, Mohammad Abdullah Al Huthaify, was a [[scholar]] and an the [[imam]] in the [[Saudi Arabian Army]]. He received his early [[education]] from the knowledgeable in his village and he completed to memorising [[Quran]] by learning at the hand of [[sheikh|Shaykh Mohammed bin Ibrahiim AlHuthaify]]. He also studied many texts in various forensic [[science]].
In 1961 he joined a school, after that he joined in the Scientific Institute, and finally he entered the Sharia’s Faculty of [[Riyadh]]. In 1972 he graduated in [[Bachelor of Laws]] from the [[Imam Muhammad bin Saud Islamic University]]. In 1975 he received a [[master’s degree]] in [[sharia|Islamic law]] from [[Al-Azhar University]] and then he took his [[doctorate]] from the same university. <ref>https://archive.org/stream/ImaamMasjidNabawiSaudiEra13451436AbdullahAhmedAlGhamidi/ImaamMasjidNabawiSaudiEra-1345-1436-AbdullahAhmedAlGhamidi#page/n466</ref>
He was an imam and Khateeb of [[Quba Mosque]] during 1978. In 1979 he became an imam of [[Al-Masjid al-Nabawi]]. In 1401, during the month of [[Ramadan]], he was appointed as imam for the [[Tarawih]] prayers in [[Masjid al-Haram]] and then he went back to [[Al-Masjid al-Nabawi|Great Mosque]] of [[Medina]] where he continues to lead salat. <ref>http://www.islamise.co.uk/islam/shaikh-ali-al-hudhaify/biography-ali-al-hudhaify</ref>
