{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | name = Ignatius Loyola Mascarenhas | title = Bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh|Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh]] | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh|Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh]] | term = 10 February 2009&nbsp;– present | predecessor = Gerald John Mathias | successor = <!-- Orders --> | ordination = | ordinated_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = 1949-06-03 | birth_place = [[Mangalore]], [[India]] [[File:Flag of India.svg|25px]] | death_date = | death_place = | previous_post = Prelate | motto = JUSTICE, LOVE, HUMILITY }}
'''Ignatius Loyola Mascarenhas''' (3 June 1949) is an [[India]]n [[prelate]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]].
Mascarenhas was born in [[Mangalore]], India.<ref>[http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=58524]</ref> He was ordained a priest on 17 December 1977. He was appointed bishop to the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh|Diocese of Simla and Chandigarh]] on 10 February 2009, and ordained bishop on 3 April 2009.<ref>[http://www.fides.org/en/news/22217-ASIA_INDIA_Bishop_of_Simla_Chandigarh_appointed#.U_bbH2PEiW8 Fides]</ref><ref>[http://www.daijiworld.com/news/news_disp.asp?n_id=58524 Daiji World for 5 April 2009]</ref> Mascarenhas is till date bishop of the Chandigarh and Simla Diocese.
