'''[[Shah#Shahzada|Shahzada]] Tara Singh [[Bahadur (title)|Bahadur]]''' (4 December 1807 – 1859) was the fourth son of [[Ranjit Singh]], Maharaja of [[Sikh Empire]] and younger twin brother [[Sher Singh]]. His mother was Maharani [[Mahtab Kaur]], family of Sandhawaila Jatt prince. but it is said that his actual mother was Manki, a Muslim slave-girl of Mai Sada Kaur. <ref>[http://www.royalark.net/India4/lahore3.htm THE PUNJAB The Sukerchukia Dynasty GENEALOGY]</ref> After the Sikh war, he died in 1859.

